SPARC PARTNERS WITH THEORETICAL ECONOMICS
TO PROVIDE TOP-QUALITY OPEN ACCESS RESEARCH

New Journal an Alternative to Two High-Priced Commercial Publications
Washington, DC =96 SPARC (the Scholarly Publishing=20
and Academic Resources Coalition) has partnered=20
with Theoretical Economics=20
(http://econtheory.org), an open access journal=20
created by the Society for Economic Theory as an=20
alternative to two high-cost publications. The=20
new, peer-reviewed outlet for high-quality=20
research in economic theory provides an=20
alternative to the Journal of Economic Theory and=20
Games and Economic Behavior, both published by Elsevier.

As an open access journal, Theoretical Economics=20
allows authors of articles to retain unrestricted=20
rights to use their articles for non-commercial=20
purposes, including the right to make and=20
distribute copies in the course of teaching and=20
research and the right to post accepted papers on=20
personal or institutional Web sites and in other=20
open access repositories. Theoretical Economics=20
submits the metadata of published papers to RePEc=20
and encourages authors to place their articles in=20
appropriate open access repositories in order to=20
render the article metadata accessible to=20
third-party search and discovery services via=20
Open Archives Initiative metadata harvesting=20
protocols. Theoretical Economics has a long-term=20
data archiving plan in place via T-Space (based=20
at the University of Toronto) to guarantee that=20
published research will be available into the future.

=93Open access journals like Theoretical Economics=20
promote the future of research, discovery and=20
learning through the timely dissemination of=20
relevant information and through mutual support=20
for scholars,=94 said Heather Joseph, SPARC=20
Director. =93As SPARC expands into the social=20
sciences, the field of economics presents a=20
promising opportunity for researchers who want=20
their work to have a global reach, and=20
Theoretical Economics uses current technology to=20
great advantage to give authors the best options=20
for publishing their articles.=94

=93Theoretical Economics aims to become the leading=20
field journal in economic theory=94, said Martin J.=20
Osborne, the Managing Editor of the journal. =93It=20
is the first open access journal to provide an=20
alternative to the top-ranked journals in the=20
field. We believe that its success will encourage=20
others to establish high-quality open access=20
journals in other fields of economics, reclaiming=20
full control by the profession of its research output.=94

Volume 1, Issue 1 of Theoretical Economics was published on March 2, 2006.

***
Society for Economic Theory
Society for Economic Theory is a non-profit=20
corporation devoted exclusively to the spread of=20
scientific knowledge in economic theory. Its=20
journal, Theoretical Economics, is on the web at http://econtheory.org.

SPARC
SPARC (Scholarly Publishing and Academic=20
Resources Coalition) and SPARC Europe are an=20
international alliance of more than 300 academic=20
and research libraries working to correct=20
imbalances in the scholarly publishing system.=20
SPARC=92s advocacy, educational, and publisher=20
partnership programs encourage expanded=20
dissemination of research. SPARC is located on=20
the Web at http://www.arl.org/sparc; SPARC Europe=20
is at http://www.sparceurope.org.

